To help slow the spread of COVID-19, keep these key times in mind for when to clean and sanitize toys and games in your childcare facility.

How to clean and sanitize toys:
- Clean plastic or rubber toys with warm soapy water. Sanitize with EPA-registered disinfectant, rinse, and air dry.
- Launder plush or cloth toys in the washing machine at warmest setting.
- Wipe down electronic or wooden toys with alcohol-based wipe or spray with 70% alcohol.

Toys that cannot be cleaned and sanitized should not be used. Learn more: https://bit.ly/3jgRVEO.

The Riceville High School Volleyball Team will be hosting a volleyball camp this summer. The camp will be held from August 3rd thru August 6th in the high school gym. 4th thru 6th grade will be from 8am - 9am. 7th and 9th grade will be from 9am - 10am. 9th thru 12th grade will be from 10am - noon. Each participant will receive a camp tank top. Camp will cost $40 per participant = payable to Riceville AAU Volleyball.

Please email RCSDVolleyball@gmail.com to register with the following information:

Name of participant

Grade in the fall

Shirt size

Contact information with cell phone number and email address

Any other pertinent information regarding the participant

All COVID-19 guidelines will be followed.

April 22 at 8:29 AM ¬∑

July 7, 2020 UPDATE: This online program has ended. All applications received on or before July 7 will be processed. To upgrade your license, make an appointment at one of our service centers at https://iowadot.gov/mvd/driverslicense/service-selector. Please plan ahead as appointments are booking several weeks out.

During this health crisis, we're allowing teens who qualify to upgrade their licenses online. If you have a learner's permit or an intermediate license and are eligible to upgrade, go to https://iowadot.gov/mvd/driverslicense/under-18.

NOTE: It could take up to five days for application processing.

Dear Wildcat Families,
By now, most of you are aware that Governor Reynolds has closed school for the remainder of the 2019-20 school year, due to COVID-19. Riceville will carry on with our meal program and voluntary continuous learning opportunities. As parents, we are sure you have many questions. Please know that the administration and staff are working through these issues, and using guidance from the Department of Education. We will send out more information next week.
We know this is a difficult time for all, as we are living it too. As always, reach out to your building administrator or Mrs. Schwamman if you have questions. The R factor is strong and as Wildcats we will get through this together!!!

Riceville Administration Team

shared_text:
Mitchell County Regional Health Center
April 3 at 7:38 AM ¬∑

Thank you for your willingness to help make masks for Mitchell County Regional Health Center! Here are a few of the face masks we received. We love them all but we will need more as we will be using them on a case-by-case basis!

Please construct masks using the following specifications put out by the Iowa Department of Public Health:
~ 100% cotton fabric, tightly woven, minimum of 160 thread count per square inch
~Ties and tape-100% cotton- white or natural color-minimum 1/4 inch thick
~Nose piece-minimum 4 inches long-plastic coated wire twist ties
~Masks size when complete- 7 inches wide by 3.75 inches long
~3 pleats per mask facing upward
~The mask should have two layers of fabric

There are many different patterns available on the internet, please choose one that meets the specifications above.

Masks are being collected in tubs outside of our St. Ansgar and Osage Clinic entrances. Please remember to leave your name and contact information with your donation!
